#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:2
msgid "Code of Conduct"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:4
msgid "Conduct"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:6
msgid ""
"We are committed to providing a friendly, safe and welcoming environment for "
"all, regardless of level of experience, gender identity and expression, "
"sexual orientation, disability, personal appearance, body size, race, "
"ethnicity, age, religion, nationality, or other similar characteristic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:8
msgid "Please be kind and courteous. There’s no need to be mean or rude."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:9
msgid ""
"Please avoid using usernames that are overtly sexual or otherwise might "
"detract from a friendly, safe, and welcoming environment for all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:10
msgid ""
"Respect that people have differences of opinion and that every design or "
"implementation choice carries trade-offs. There is seldom a single right "
"answer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:11
msgid ""
"We borrow the Recurse Center’s [“social rules”](https://www.recurse.com/"
"manual#sub-sec-social-rules): no feigning surprise, no well-actually’s, no "
"backseat driving, and no subtle -isms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:12
msgid ""
"Please keep unstructured critique to a minimum. If you have solid ideas you "
"want to experiment with, make a fork and see how it works. All feedback "
"should be constructive in nature. If you need more detailed guidance around "
"giving feedback, consult [Digital Ocean’s Code of Conduct](https://github."
"com/digitalocean/engineering-code-of-conduct#giving-and-receiving-feedback)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:13
msgid ""
"It is unacceptable to insult, demean, or harass anyone. We interpret the "
"term “harassment” as defined in the [Citizen Code of Conduct](https://github."
"com/stumpsyn/policies/blob/master/citizen_code_of_conduct.md#4-unacceptable-"
"behavior); if you are not sure about what harassment entails, please read "
"their definition. In particular, we don’t tolerate behavior that excludes "
"people in socially marginalized groups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:14
msgid ""
"Private harassment is also unacceptable. No matter who you are, please "
"contact any of the Pyodide core team members immediately if you are being "
"harassed or made uncomfortable by a community member. Whether you are a "
"regular contributor or a newcomer, we care about making this community a "
"safe place for you and we’ve got your back."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:15
msgid ""
"Likewise spamming, trolling, flaming, baiting or other attention-stealing "
"behavior is not welcome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:17
msgid "Moderation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:19
msgid ""
"These are the policies for upholding our community’s standards of conduct. "
"If you feel that a thread needs moderation, please contact the Pyodide core "
"team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:21
msgid ""
"Remarks that violate the Pyodide standards of conduct are not allowed. This "
"includes hateful, hurtful, oppressive, or exclusionary remarks. (Cursing is "
"allowed, but never targeting another community member, and never in a "
"hateful manner.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:22
msgid ""
"Remarks that moderators find inappropriate are not allowed, even if they do "
"not break a rule explicitly listed in the code of conduct."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:23
msgid "Moderators will first respond to such remarks with a warning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:24
msgid ""
"If the warning is unheeded, the offending community member will be "
"temporarily banned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:25
msgid ""
"If the community member comes back and continues to make trouble, they will "
"be permanently banned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:26
msgid ""
"Moderators may choose at their discretion to un-ban the community member if "
"they offer the offended party a genuine apology."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:27
msgid ""
"If a moderator bans someone and you think it was unjustified, please take it "
"up with that moderator, or with a different moderator, in private. "
"Complaints about bans in-channel are not allowed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:28
msgid ""
"Moderators are held to a higher standard than other community members. If a "
"moderator creates an inappropriate situation, they should expect less leeway "
"than others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:29
msgid ""
"In the Pyodide community we strive to go the extra mile to look out for each "
"other. Don’t just aim to be technically unimpeachable, try to be your best "
"self. In particular, avoid flirting with offensive or sensitive issues, "
"particularly if they’re off-topic; this all too often leads to unnecessary "
"fights, hurt feelings, and damaged trust; worse, it can drive people away "
"from the community entirely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:30
msgid ""
"If someone takes issue with something you said or did, resist the urge to be "
"defensive. Just stop doing what it was they complained about and apologize. "
"Even if you feel you were misinterpreted or unfairly accused, chances are "
"good there was something you could have communicated better — remember that "
"it’s your responsibility to make your fellow Pyodide community members "
"comfortable. Everyone wants to get along and we are all here first and "
"foremost because we want to talk about science and cool technology. You will "
"find that people will be eager to assume good intent and forgive as long as "
"you earn their trust."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:31
msgid ""
"The enforcement policies listed above apply to all official Pyodide venues. "
"If you wish to use this code of conduct for your own project, consider "
"making a copy with your own moderation policy so as to avoid confusion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md:33
msgid ""
"Adapted from the [Rust Code of Conduct](https://www.rust-lang.org/en-US/"
"conduct.html), with further reference from [Digital Ocean Code of Conduct]"
"(https://github.com/digitalocean/engineering-code-of-conduct#giving-and-"
"receiving-feedback), the [Recurse Center](https://www.recurse.com/code-of-"
"conduct), the [Citizen Code of Conduct](http://citizencodeofconduct.org/), "
"and the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/"
"version/1/4/code-of-conduct.html)."
msgstr ""
